- data structure in computer science that stores information about the active functions 
(or subroutines) of a running computer program

### EXAMPLE 3 (Main and GreaterThan Function)

A.R. (Activation Record) of int main() {

int x = 5, y = 6;
num = greaterThan(x,y);
printf("%d", num);
}

